subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia
with aedeagus in lateral view (
Fig. 12f
) curved, apex acutely pointed, recurved dorsally. In ventral view (
Fig. 12g
), aedeagus with a longitudinal depression along middle of ventral side, depression being stronger distally; aedeagus narrowed apically forming a triangular denticle. Dorsal opening (
Fig. 12h
) partially covered with three laminae.

